</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="186" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark, 2022" authorityName="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,499,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[329,354,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[371,395,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[412,499,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[507,598,150,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[507,598,150,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
belongs to the group of species with inferior ocular lobes shorter than the genae and elytra with pale yellowish pubescence. It differs from nearly all species of the group by sides of scutellum being dark.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="186" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,258,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark, 2022" authorityName="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,489,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[322,346,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[362,386,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[402,489,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[495,584,258,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[495,584,258,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1939" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1939" box="[729,1248,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[729,818,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[834,923,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Bisaltes</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[938,1065,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">brevicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[1071,1248,258,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="144 - 290" refId="ref2410" refString="Breuning, S. (1939) Novae species Cerambycidarum VII. Festschrift zum 60. Geburtstage von Professor Dr. Embrik Strand, Riga, 5, 144 - 290." type="journal article" year="1939">Breuning, 1939</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, it differs by the inferior ocular lobes of the eyes being shorter than the genae (as long as genae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1939" box="[1178,1377,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[1178,1202,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1211,1236,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1251,1377,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), antennomere III not exposing integument (exposing integument on distal one-fourth in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1939" box="[1098,1304,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[1098,1122,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1138,1162,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1178,1304,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), scutellum small with wide central pubescence not forming longitudinal band (scutellum large with slender central pubescence forming longitudinal band in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1939" box="[490,701,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[490,514,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[533,557,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[575,701,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), oblique longitudinal yellowish white pubescent band reaching humerus and attaining the suture almost before the middle (not reaching humerus and attaining the suture beyond the middle in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1939" box="[306,513,474,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[306,330,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[346,371,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[387,513,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Bezark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Silva, A." box="[357,589,510,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="9 - 16" refId="ref2524" refString="Galileo, M. H. M., Bezark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Silva, A. (2016) Descriptions of three new species and new records of Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) from America. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 63 (1), 9 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / dez. 63.6615" type="journal article" year="2016">
Galileo 
<emphasis box="[448,499,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[647,810,510,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" refId="ref2659" refString="Monne, M. A. (2022) Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical region. Part II. Subfamily Lamiinae. Available from: https: // cerambycids. com / catalog / (accessed 1 June 2022)" type="url" year="2022">Monné (2022)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1966" box="[818,1099,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscomarmoratus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[818,843,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[860,885,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[903,1099,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">fuscomarmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[1294,1387,510,536]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,206,547,573]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Peru</collectingCountry>
. However, the specimens collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[673,766,546,572]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
identified by Martins as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1966" box="[1052,1331,546,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscomarmoratus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[1052,1077,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1094,1118,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1135,1331,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">fuscomarmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the collection of LGBC (
<bibRefCitation author="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Bezark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Silva, A." box="[387,598,582,609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="9 - 16" refId="ref2524" refString="Galileo, M. H. M., Bezark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Silva, A. (2016) Descriptions of three new species and new records of Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) from America. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 63 (1), 9 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / dez. 63.6615" type="journal article" year="2016">
Galileo 
<emphasis box="[478,526,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) is 
<taxonomicName authority="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark, 2022" authorityName="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2022" box="[637,804,582,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[637,661,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[677,701,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[717,804,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,899,582,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[810,899,582,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, therefore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1966" box="[1027,1303,582,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscomarmoratus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[1027,1052,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1067,1092,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1107,1303,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">fuscomarmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is excluded from the Ecuadorian fauna. 
<taxonomicName authority="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark, 2022" authorityName="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2022" box="[462,629,618,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[462,487,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[502,526,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[542,629,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[635,724,618,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[635,724,618,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1966" box="[871,1146,618,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscomarmoratus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[871,895,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[910,935,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[950,1146,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">fuscomarmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows: antennomeres V, VII and IX exposing the integument on distal three-fourths (totally exposing the integument on antennomeres V, VII and IX in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1966" box="[311,589,690,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscomarmoratus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[311,336,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[352,377,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[393,589,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">fuscomarmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); elytra with fulvous pubescence (elytra with pale yellowish pubescence in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,428,726,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscomarmoratus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[151,176,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[192,216,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[232,428,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">fuscomarmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<taxonomicName authority="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark, 2022" authorityName="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2022" box="[199,369,762,788]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[199,224,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[241,265,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[282,369,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[378,469,762,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[378,469,762,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be included in the alternative of couplet “24”, from 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[1115,1302,762,788]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" pagination="209 - 335" refId="ref2479" refString="Breuning, S. (1971) Revision des especes americaines de la tribu des Apomecynini Lac. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Abhandlungen und Berichte aus dem staatlichen Museum fur Tierkunde in Dresden, 37 (3), 209 - 335." type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning (1971)</bibRefCitation>
(translated; modified):
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,867,1006]" box="[151,1436,867,889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">23 Elytra with pale yellowish pubescence or vaguely mottled with light brown pubescence............................ 24</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,867,1006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
24(23) Inferior ocular lobes of eyes as long as genae; antennomere III exposing integument at distal one-fourth; scutellum with slender central pubescence forming longitudinal band................................................. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1939" box="[1258,1436,926,947]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[1258,1280,926,947]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1293,1315,926,947]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1328,1436,926,947]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,867,1006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
- Inferior ocular lobes of eyes shorter than genae; antennomere III not exposing integument; scutellum with wide central pubescence not forming longitudinal band.................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark, 2022" authorityName="Juárez-Noé &amp; González-Coronado &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2022" box="[1210,1354,985,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[1210,1231,985,1006]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1244,1266,985,1006]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1279,1354,985,1006]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1360,1436,985,1006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,985,1006]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="186" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1053,1115]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1053,1079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet comes from the Latin “confusa” meaning “confusing”, in reference to the fact that the new species was originally incorrectly identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1966" box="[822,1099,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscomarmoratus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[822,847,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[863,887,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[903,1099,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="186">fuscomarmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
